<HEADLINE> Starzz 83, Fire 73  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Natalie Williams scored 25 points and
grabbed 11 rebounds as the Utah Starzz beat the Portland Fire 83-73
Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   Michelle VanGorp led Portland with 16 points. Tara Williams
added 15 and Michelle Marciniak had 10 for the Fire (10-21).
</P>
<P>
   The Fire were down by 11 early, but cut the Starzz lead to two
just before halftime. That was as close as Portland would come.
</P>
<P>
   Trailing by as many as 15 in the second half, Portland got
within nine with four minutes to go. Utah was 6-of-10 from the foul
line in the final minutes to close out the game.
</P>
<P>
   The Starzz (17-14) were without Adrienne Goodson, out with an
injury. Her replacement, LaTonya Johnson, scored 10 points. Cory
Hlede added 11 for Utah.
</P>
</TEXT>
