<HEADLINE> US Exchange Student Killed in Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LISMORE, Australia (AP) -- An exchange student was killed and
three other Americans seriously injured in a car collision, police
said.
</P>
<P>
   Gina Maree Rosko, 21, of Kenosha, Wis., was killed instantly in
the crash near Lismore, 370 miles north of Sydney, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The group of Americans was traveling in a Toyota sedan that
apparently crossed into the oncoming lane around a curve and
crashed into a dump truck, police said. The truck driver was not
injured.
</P>
<P>
   The sedan driver, whose name was not released, was airlifted to
a Brisbane hospital for serious leg and internal injuries.
Passengers Luke Nowel, 21, of Milwaukee, and Theresea Baker, 20, of
Wauhatosa, Wis., were being treated in Lismore Base Hospital with
serious injuries.
</P>
