<HEADLINE> Plaza Hotel security guards shoot burglary suspect  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - Security guards at the Central Park south
landmark Plaza Hotel chased a burglary suspect through the lobby
and shot him outside.
</P>
<P>
   The suspect, who was not identified, was approached in the lobby
about 9 p.m. Monday by guards who recognized him from surveillance
videotapes taken during a previous theft, police said.
</P>
<P>
   As the suspect left the hotel, he pulled a gun and fired shots
at the guards, prompting one of them to fire one shot back, hitting
him in the arm, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Witnesses described a wild scene as the fleeing suspect, wearing
a blue suit and tie, skirted around the William Tecumseh Sherman
statue in front of the hotel and hopped into a taxi at 60th Street
and Fifth Avenue, about a block away.
</P>
<P>
   Police cars hemmed the taxi in. The suspect jumped out of the
cab and was wrestled to the ground by police officers, witnesses
said.
</P>
<P>
   Fifth Avenue was closed between 60th and 62nd streets for about
two hours while police interviewed witnesses and combed the area
for shell casings.
</P>
<P>
   The suspect was taken to St. Clair's Hospital, where he was
listed in stable condition.
</P>
<P>
   No other injuries were reported.
</P>
<P>
   Telephone calls to the Plaza Hotel were unanswered.
</P>
</TEXT>
