<HEADLINE> Geneseo professor Charles R. Bailey dies  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) - State University College at Geneseo
history professor, Charles R. ''Randy'' Bailey, has died of cancer
at 62.
</P>
<P>
   Bailey, a member of the SUNY Geneseo faculty since 1967, was
serving as chairman of the history department at the time of his
death last Friday.
</P>
<P>
   SUNY named Bailey a distinguished service professor in 1997, a
title that promoted him above full professor.
</P>
<P>
   ''Randy Bailey served the college in uniquely valuable ways for
33 years,'' SUNY Geneseo President Christopher C. Dahl said. ''He
was remarkable for his contributions to his departments and to
statewide organizations, and for his enthusiastic support of
cultural and intellectual life on campus.''
</P>
<P>
   Born in Unionville Center, Ohio, Bailey earned his bachelor's
degree from Ohio University in Athens in 1960. He received a
master's degree and doctorate from the University of Chicago.
</P>
<P>
   He was a specialist in early modern history and the history of
education. He published two books and many articles, which gained
him a reputation as an important scholar in the field of the French
Revolution.
</P>
<P>
   He is survived by his wife, Susan Ferrall Bailey of Geneseo; two
daughters, Kate Bailey of Santa Monica, Calif., and Rachel Bailey
of Rochester; his mother, Alberta Bailey of Unionville Center; and
two brothers, Larry Bailey of Danville, Va., and Joseph Bailey of
Perrysburg, Ohio.
</P>
<P>
   A memorial service will be 2 p.m. Tuesday in the Alice Austin
Theatre in the William A. Brodie Fine Arts Building on the SUNY
Geneseo campus.
</P>
<P>
   Burial will be in Lancaster, Ohio.
</P>
</TEXT>
