<HEADLINE> Dangerfield To Release 'My 5 Wives'  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Rodney Dangerfield is back and he's feeling
funny.
</P>
<P>
   The comic who became a household name with his ''I get no
respect'' standup banter and on-screen buffoonery has recovered
from heart bypass surgery and is about to release a film called
''My 5 Wives.''
</P>
<P>
   ''I was inspired to write the story because my wife is a Mormon
and I became fascinated with the whole polygamy thing. I thought,
what a great idea for a film,'' he said Monday. ''Polygamy's still
practiced in over 50 countries.''
</P>
<P>
   Set in the fictional town of Redwood Falls, Utah, ''My 5 Wives''
is not about the Mormon religion but instead a lighthearted look at
polygamy. It will be released nationwide Sept. 8.
</P>
<P>
   ''One of the advantages of having five wives is they can't all
have a headache at the same time,'' Dangerfield said.
</P>
<P>
   The 78-year-old comic's other movie credits include
''Caddyshack,'' ''Easy Money'' and ''Back to School.''
</P>
<P>
   In March, Dangerfield underwent double bypass surgery in Los
Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   ''I shook it off,'' Dangerfield said when asked about his
health.
</P>
