</P>
<P>
   For the second time in two weeks, the group was forced to flee a
stage Sunday night when it was pelted with plastic bottles and
other objects before a crowd of 30,000 at the Sudoeste festival.
</P>
<P>
   Oasis, currently on a world tour, also cut a concert short at a
Swiss rock festival last month after concertgoers threw bottles and
cans on stage.
</P>
<P>
   Oasis blamed the latest incident on a small group of
troublemakers, but festival producers blamed the disruption on the
band.
