<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Business news in brief from around New Jersey  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   MOUNT ARLINGTON, N.J. (AP) - Software developer Telelogic of
Stockholm, Sweden, announced Tuesday that it is acquiring Quality
Systems and Software Inc., based in Mount Arlington.
</P>
<P>
   Telelogic will pay $115 million in stock for the privately held
management solutions provider. QSS had sales of $29.5 million last
year and employs 230 people.
</P>
<P>
   The deal, which needs to be approved by U.S. regulatory
authorities, would almost double the Swedish company's sales
capacity in the United States. Chief executive Anders Lidbeck said
he hoped to complete the deal by September.
</P>
<P>
   SADDLE BROOK, N.J. (AP) - The Home Depot, the nation's largest
home improvement retailer, will open its third Villager's Hardware
store in New Jersey here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Villager's Hardware stores are about one-third the size of the
warehouse-style Home Depots and carry tools, garden supplies and
paint.
</P>
<P>
   The first store opened in June 1999, filling a vacant Rickel
Home Center in East Brunswick. The other store opened in Garwood
last November, and a fourth store is scheduled to open in Elizabeth
this fall.
</P>
<P>
   Home Depot, based in Atlanta, has more than 1,000 stores in the
United States, Puerto Rico, Canada and Chile, and 38 in New Jersey.
The retailer employs approximately 226,000 people.
</P>
<P>
   ALLENDALE, N.J. (AP) - Cadapult Graphic Systems Inc., a computer
graphics firm, said Tuesday that it will begin trading on the
American Stock Exchange, beginning Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The Allendale-based company will trade under the symbol GFX. It
had been trading over-the-counter under the symbol GRFX.
</P>
<P>
   Cadapult Graphic Systems has regional offices in Boston,
Philadelphia and Redmond, Wash. Its subsidiary, Media Sciences
Inc., manufactures color printer supplies.
</P>
<P>
   FLORHAM PARK, N.J. (AP) - Administaff Inc., a personnel
management company, said it will open a sales office here to serve
small and medium-sized businesses in the area.
</P>
<P>
   The new office is part of a nationwide expansion that includes
the creation of 90 sales offices in 40 markets. The Houston-based
company now has 29 offices in 17 metropolitan areas.
</P>
<P>
   Joe Ringwood will serve as district manager for New Jersey.
</P>
<P>
   LAWRENCEVILLE, N.J. (AP) - Princeton Video Image Inc. said
Tuesday that it has received its seventh U.S. patent for image
insertion in television broadcasts.
</P>
<P>
   The new technology stabilizes virtual images, such as
advertisements. With previous technology, the advertisement would
jiggle on the screen instead of appearing as a fixed part of the
scene.
</P>
<P>
   PVI, based in Princeton, provides video insertion services for
Major League Baseball, NFL football, auto races and other televised
sports events.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
