<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that were moving substantially or trading
heavily Tuesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
   Verizon Communications Inc., down $5.812 at $42.063
</P>
<P>
   The New York-based telecommunications company formed by the
merger of Bell Atlantic and GTE, which has been struck by
communications workers, said its full-year earnings will fall short
of forecasts.
</P>
<P>
   Dial Corp., down 87.5 cents at $11.938
</P>
<P>
   The Scottsdale, Ariz.-maker of Dial soap announced the
resignation of its chairman and CEO and said it will miss earnings
estimates for the full year.
</P>
<P>
   Lowe's Cos., up 75 cents at $45.75
</P>
<P>
   The Wilkesboro, N.C.-based home improvement retailer will
eliminate from its warehouse stores wood products from endangered
forests.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
   Lemount &AMP; Hauspie Speech Products NV, down $7.187 at $29.813
</P>
<P>
   The Burlington, Mass.-based maker of speech recognition software
may have given incorrect data to its South Korean customers. The
company disputes the assertion.
</P>
<P>
   Siebel Systems Inc., up $10.187 at $174.375
</P>
<P>
   The San Mateo Calif.-based maker of software for managed
customer relations announced a 2-for-1 stock split.
</P>
<P>
   Staples Inc., up $2.25 at $17.563
</P>
<P>
   The Boston-based office-supplies chain said its second-quarter
profits will likely top Wall Street forecasts.
</P>
</TEXT>
