<HEADLINE> AmerGen buys Oyster Creek nuclear plant  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   FORKED RIVER, N.J. (AP) - AmerGen, a joint venture between PECO
Energy Co. and the largest energy generator in the United Kingdom,
bought the Oyster Creek Nuclear Generating Station on Tuesday for
$10 million.
</P>
<P>
   With the sale, Morristown-based GPU Inc., ceased generating
energy.
</P>
<P>
   ''We are now sharply focused on the transmission and
distribution of electricity, as well as new, non-regulated
businesses,'' said Fred D. Hafer, GPU chairman, president and CEO.
</P>
<P>
   Oyster Creek's 636 employees became AmerGen employees with the
sale, said Bill Jones, AmerGen spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   ''There will be reviews of staff levels down the road, but no
immediate reduction in force,'' Jones said.
</P>
<P>
   The sale includes the 619-megawatt reactor and adjacent
property.
</P>
<P>
   AmerGen Energy Co., a joint venture of Philadelphia-based PECO
Energy Co. and British Energy Co. of Scotland, now holds the
license for Oyster's Creek's operation.
</P>
<P>
   The U.S. Nuclear Regulatory Commission approved the license
transfer in June and the New Jersey Board of Public Utilities
approved the sale on July 20.
</P>
<P>
   GPU Inc. had planned to close the plant this year if it didn't
find a buyer.
</P>
<P>
   AmerGen will assume responsibility for the ultimate
decommissioning of Oyster Creek. Its current license expires in
2009, Jones said, but AmerGen could apply for a license extension.
</P>
<P>
   GPU on Tuesday turned over $440 million to AmerGen as its share
of the decommissioning costs, said Ned Raynolds, GPU spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   AmerGen last year bought Three Mile Island Unit 1 in Middletown,
Pa., and the Clinton Power Station in Clinton, Ill. The company has
signed a purchase agreement for the Vermont Yankee Nuclear Power
Station in Vermont.
</P>
<P>
   ---
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: Nuclear Regulatory Commission: www.nrc.gov
</P>
<P>
   PECO Energy: www.peco.com
</P>
<P>
   British Energy: www.british-energy.co.uk
</P>
<P>
   Nuclear Information and Resource Service: www.nirs.org
</P>
</TEXT>
