<HEADLINE> Reds' Aaron Boone Has Knee Surgery  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CINCINNATI (AP) -- Cincinnati Reds third baseman Aaron Boone had
reconstructive surgery Tuesday for a torn anterior cruciate
ligament in his left knee.
</P>
<P>
   Doctors initially thought Boone had only a partial tear, but
discovered during surgery that it was completely torn, team doctor
Timothy Kremchek said.
</P>
<P>
   Boone should be able to run in 8-12 weeks and should be
completely healed by spring training, Kremchek said.
</P>
<P>
   ''We'll push him hard,'' he said. ''He wants us to push him
hard.''
</P>
<P>
   Boone, who hurt the knee while fielding on July 5, batted .285
in 84 games with 12 homers and 43 RBIs.
</P>
</TEXT>
