<HEADLINE> Lieberman Avoided Vietnam War Draft  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Sen. Joseph I. Lieberman, the running mate of
Democrat Al Gore,
avoided serving in the Vietnam War with two deferments, one as a
student and another for being a father, Eric Kleiman, a spokesman,
said Tuesday.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Lieberman, a Connecticut Democrat, graduated from Yale College
in 1964. He attended Yale Law School for the next three years,
graduating in 1967.
</P>
<P>
   --Vice President Gore served five months in Vietnam as an Army
reporter.
</P>
<P>
   Neither GOP presidential nominee George W. Bush nor his running
mate, former Defense Secretary Dick Cheney, went to Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
   --Bush served in the Texas Air National Guard.
</P>
<P>
   --Cheney avoided military service with deferments as a student
and expectant father.
</P>
</TEXT>
