<HEADLINE> McCrimmon Named Flames Ass't Coach  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CALGARY, Alberta (AP) -- Brad McCrimmon, a former Flames captain,
was hired by the team Tuesday to be an assistant under new coach
Don Hay.
</P>
<P>
   McCrimmon served as the head coach of Saskatoon of the Western
Hockey League the past two seasons.
</P>
<P>
   ''Brad brings a wealth of experience and leadership to our
coaching staff,'' general manager Craig Button said. ''He has had
success both as a player and as a young coach.''
</P>
<P>
   McCrimmon played with three seasons with the Flames and was a
member of the 1989 team that won the Stanley Cup. The defenseman
served as the team captain during the 1989-90 season, his last in
Calgary.
</P>
</TEXT>
