<HEADLINE> Liberty 57, Rockers 44  </HEADLINE>
By MELISSA MURPHY
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The New York Liberty, led by Tari Phillips' 14
points, clinched their second consecutive Eastern Conference title
with a 57-44 victory over the Cleveland Rockers Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Crystal Robinson and Becky Hammon added 11 points apiece for the
Liberty, who extended a franchise record with their 10th straight
home victory before a crowd of 18,663 at Madison Square Garden.
</P>
<P>
   New York (20-11), winners of 13 of 15, will face either
Washington or Detroit in the first round of the Eastern Conference
playoffs beginning Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Merlakia Jones had 21 points and was the only player in double
figures for the second-place Rockers (17-14), who have dropped five
of six road games. Cleveland has already clinched a playoff spot
</P>
<P>
   Phillips had 11 rebounds and two steals and Teresa Weatherspoon
added seven assists and six steals for New York.
</P>
<P>
   The Rockers committed 19 turnovers that were converted into 17
Liberty points.
</P>
<P>
   New York led 53-41 before Jones' 3-pointer brought the Rockers
within nine points with 2:15 remaining. The Liberty held the
Rockers scoreless the rest of the way as Phillips hit a baseline
jumper and Robinson added a basket to close out the game.
</P>
<P>
   Cleveland got within 36-32 with 12 minutes remaining on
consecutive jumpers by Jones and a basket by Rushia Brown. The
Liberty missed 10 of 14 shots in that span before taking a 49-38
lead with five minutes left.
</P>
<P>
   Hammon had seven points and Robinson added six in the 13-6 run.
</P>
<P>
   The Rockers, who shot just 29 percent in the first half, trailed
28-19 at halftime.
</P>
<P>
   The Liberty tied a team record with their 12th home victory
after a 2-4 start. They went 12-3 at home in 1998 and 12-4 last
season. New York won seven straight home games spanning the 1997
and 1998 seasons.
</P>
</TEXT>
