<HEADLINE> Shaq Pays For New L.A. Police Car  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Shaquille O'Neal's check for $42,893 to buy a
new Los Angeles police patrol car was formally accepted by the
city's Police Commission on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   O'Neal sent the check two days after the Los Angeles Lakers won
the NBA championship in June, to replace one of two police cars
burned when a downtown fan celebration turned to vandalism.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers organization also sent a check for the same amount
last week to pay for another replacement vehicle, team spokesman
John Black said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   O'Neal, the 7-foot-1, 330-pound center who won the league
regular season and NBA Finals MVP awards, specified the money be
used for a full-service black-and-white.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to the two patrol cars burned, roving celebrants
also damaged two television news vans and vandalized some downtown
businesses. Eleven people were arrested, but no serious injuries
were reported.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
