<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More than 4,500 soldiers to attend mock deployment at last year's Woodstock site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROME, N.Y. (AP) - Last year it was an invasion of Woodstock
fans. This year? The Army.
</P>
<P>
   Some 6,500 National Guard and Army reserve troops will
participate in Exercise Empire Peak, a mock deployment being staged
Aug. 12-19 at Griffiss Business and Technology Park, formerly the
Griffiss air base.
</P>
<P>
   The exercise will be overseen by the Air Force Base Conversion
Agency.
</P>
<P>
   The mock deployment area dubbed ''Fortina'' will be a staging
area where reserves will learn the preparation procedures ranging
from the Army's arriving at a destination to its engagement in
battle. The mock battle will be staged the following week at Fort
Drum.
</P>
<P>
   There will also be an area for marksmanship training, and a
large area which will house 800 Army vehicles, 60 helicopters, and
a few C-130 aircraft. The troops will come from as far away as Ohio
and represent 12 states.
</P>
</TEXT>
